===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Bodman (1980)}} compares it to {{cog|bo|ཕྱུག||rich; wealthy}}, {{m|bo|ཕྱུགས||all beasts that can be domesticated or subjugated by man; cattle}}, but the vowels do not match with Chinese ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

{{zh-ref|Sagart (1999)}} relates it to {{och-l|寶}}, but see there for more. In later work, {{zh-ref|Sagart (2011b, 2017d)}} connects it to {{cog|tbq-pro|*pʷak||pig}}, comparing the semantic development from “pig” to “rich” to {{cog|la|pecunia||money}}, which is derived from {{cog|la|pecu||cattle; domestic animals}}, and tentatively reconstructs {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*C-pək|*C.pək|pig}}. However, the {{cog|tbq}} word for “pig” is usually compared to {{och-l|豝|sow}}.

Cognate with {{och-l|福|blessing}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

;"Fu county"
:Near-homophonous replacement of the lesser known character {{l|zh|鄜}} in 1964.

